<p>lets say, in our system when an user registers, he gets a voucher too right away. There are 3 solutions:</p>  <p>1,</p>  <pre><code>class UserModel {     public function create ($username)     {         $userId = SQL INSERT INTO users         Voucer::create ($userId);     } } </code></pre>  <p>but its bad (hurt <code>SRP</code> and <code>LoD</code>)</p>  <p>2,</p>  <pre><code>class ModelHelper {     public static function create ($username)     {         $userId = UserModel::create ($userName);         Voucer::create ($userId);     } } </code></pre>  <p>it only hurts <code>LoD</code> now.</p>  <p>3, a solution using <code>Observer Pattern</code> (Im not going to provide a source code right here).</p>  <p>So which is the best?</p>